        "title": "feat(whatsapp): notify sender after pairing approval",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add WhatsApp approval notifications to the existing channel pairing `--notify` path by wiring the plugin pairing adapter through `sendMessageWhatsApp`.\n- Reuse the shared `PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE` while preserving WhatsApp allowlist normalization.\n- Add and fix focused WhatsApp pairing coverage for the notification send path and normalization.\n\nFixes #56619.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts src/cli/pairing-cli.test.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Approving a WhatsApp pairing request with notification enabled now sends the shared pairing-approved message back through the WhatsApp send path, while preserving WhatsApp allowlist normalization.\n\nReal environment tested: Local full OpenClaw checkout on PR branch `codex/whatsapp-pairing-approval-notify-56619-20260618`, exercising the WhatsApp pairing adapter, pairing CLI channel wiring, and shared pairing adapter helpers through the repository Vitest harness after the patch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts src/cli/pairing-cli.test.ts src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.test.ts --reporter=verbose\ngit diff --check origin/main...HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the focused WhatsApp pairing run showed the notification path and adapter behavior passing:\n\n```text\n✓ |extension-whatsapp| extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts > whatsapp pairing > notifies the approved sender through the WhatsApp send path\n✓ |extension-whatsapp| extensions/whatsapp/src/channel.pairing.test.ts > whatsapp pairing > keeps WhatsApp allowlist normalization on the pairing adapter\n✓ |cli| src/cli/pairing-cli.test.ts > pairing cli > forwards --account for approve\n✓ |channels| src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.test.ts > pairing adapters > builds text pairing adapters\n✓ |channels| src/channels/plugins/pairing-adapters.test.ts > pairing adapters > builds logger-backed approval notifiers\n\n[test] passed 3 Vitest shards in 6.47s\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The WhatsApp test verifies `notifyApproval` calls `sendMessageWhatsApp` with the approved sender id, shared approval message, account id, and config; the normalization test verifies WhatsApp-prefixed phone entries still normalize correctly; CLI and shared adapter tests remain green. `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD` produced no output.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live WhatsApp transport session was not started in this environment; the focused plugin pairing tests exercise the changed approval notification path without external WhatsApp credentials.\n",
